'''Adwr Cadarn''' was an [[elf|elven]] scout from the [[Cadarn Clan]].{{CiteNPC|npc=The great divide|quote=Soon it was decided to send five members of the Cadarn clan through the Well of Voyage, to recover any information that could tell us what was happening.|name=Underground Pass}} He was sent to [[Prifddinas]] along with four other scouts during the [[Fourth Age]] to uncover the cause of the communication breakdown between Prifddinas and the other elven colonies that had settled to the east of [[Arandar]] in [[Misthalin]], [[Asgarnia]], and [[Kandarin]].{{NamedRef|Underground Pass}}

Adwr and the other four scouts travelled through the [[Underground Pass (dungeon)|Underground Pass]] that ran beneath the mountain range separating [[Tirannwn]] from Kandarin{{NamedRef|Underground Pass}} and saw the chaos of an elven civil war in Prifddinas.{{CiteNPC|npc=The great divide|quote=He told us of the chaos he had seen; elves killing elves in the streets of Prifddinas and the seizing of the Tower of Voices by clan Iorwerth.|name=Civil war}} Only Adwr survived the return trip{{CiteNPC|npc=The great divide|quote=After a few weeks, Adwr returned, the only one of the five scouts that made it back.}} to spread the news of [[Iorwerth Clan]]'s treason and subsequent conquering of [[Prifddinas]] and the [[Tower of Voices]].{{NamedRef|Civil war}}

